    narr:childCount "29"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers aswritten.ai's positioning narratives around one thesis: [the next bottleneck is missing organizational context, not model capability](narr:Claim_WorldviewBottleneck). The competitive frame is a [three-layer model](narr:Claim_ThreeLayerModel) — [Creation](narr:Narrative_CreationGap) (knowledge must be *extracted*, not retrieved), [Architecture](narr:Narrative_ArchitectureGap) (narrative ontology with conviction levels steers rather than dilutes), and [Infrastructure](narr:Narrative_InfrastructureGap) (worldview as git-native code in CI/CD). Around these sit product claims: [worldview as versioned code](narr:Narrative_OrgKnowledgeAsCode), [Salon recast as a per-memory capability](narr:Narrative_SalonAsCapability) rather than a deployment pattern (per the [revised taxonomy](narr:Observation_TaxonomyRevision)), [citations as constellations](narr:Narrative_CiteConstellationModel) instead of single matched claims (witnessed 2026-05-23), and [agentic coherence / back-pressure](narr:Narrative_AgenticCoherence) as the workflow rationale. Go-to-market threads run alongside: the [fundraising arc](narr:Obs_FundraisingStory), the [two-call structure](narr:Obs_TwoCallStructure), and a [decision to retire zero-context language](narr:Narrative_RetireZeroContext). Several framings are explicitly in motion — demos, sales structure, and Salon's classification have all been reframed.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_1> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_AgenticBackPressure> ;
